---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="Safe Weight Loss: How Much Per Week is Healthy?" description="Safe weight loss per week explained. The science behind sustainable fat loss vs crash dieting — know what really works." keywords="healthy weight loss, weight loss per week, safe weight loss rate, sustainable diet, fat loss rate, how fast lose weight, weight loss guide">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Health</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Safe Weight Loss: How Much Per Week is Healthy?" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">July 21, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>Quick-fix diets promise dramatic results, but what does science say about a safe and sustainable rate of weight loss? Going too fast can backfire — here is the evidence-based approach.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">The Recommended Rate</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">0.5 - 1 kg per week (1-2 lbs per week)</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">This requires a daily deficit of 500-1,000 calories</p>
      </div>
      <p>Most health organisations (NHS, CDC, WHO) recommend losing no more than 0.5-1 kg (1-2 lbs) per week for sustainable results. People with more weight to lose may safely lose faster initially.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">The Maths of Fat Loss</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>1 kg of body fat contains approximately 7,700 calories of energy</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>To lose 0.5 kg/week: deficit of about 550 calories/day</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>To lose 1 kg/week: deficit of about 1,100 calories/day</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>This can come from eating less, moving more, or both</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Why Slower is Better</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Preserves muscle:</strong> Rapid weight loss causes significant muscle loss alongside fat</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Sustainable habits:</strong> Small changes you can maintain beat dramatic ones you abandon</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Metabolic adaptation:</strong> Extreme deficits cause your metabolism to slow more than moderate ones</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Nutrient adequacy:</strong> Very low calorie diets often miss essential vitamins and minerals</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Gallstones:</strong> Rapid weight loss increases risk of gallstone formation</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Rebound weight gain:</strong> 80% of people who lose weight rapidly regain it within 2 years</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Realistic Timeline</h2>
      <p>At a safe rate of 0.5-1 kg/week:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>5 kg (11 lbs):</strong> 5-10 weeks</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>10 kg (22 lbs):</strong> 10-20 weeks (2.5-5 months)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>20 kg (44 lbs):</strong> 20-40 weeks (5-10 months)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>30 kg (66 lbs):</strong> 30-60 weeks (7-15 months)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Why the Scale Fluctuates</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Water retention:</strong> Can mask fat loss (especially after starting exercise or eating more carbs)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Food in your system:</strong> The weight of food and drink consumed but not yet processed</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Hormonal cycles:</strong> Women may retain 1-3 kg of water weight during their menstrual cycle</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Sodium intake:</strong> A salty meal can cause 1-2 kg of water retention the next day</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>Focus on the weekly trend rather than daily numbers. A moving average over 7 days gives you the true picture.</p>

      <p>This information is for general education only. Consult a healthcare professional or registered dietitian before starting any weight loss programme, especially if you have existing health conditions.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/tools/bmi" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open BMI Calculator →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/tools/bmi" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Tool →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
